<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<theorem xmlns="Theorem"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         type="Proposition"
         id="Thm_ColumnSpaceLinearMap"
         xsi:schemaLocation="Theorem file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle/mod/msm/NewSchemas/Theorem.xsd">
   <caption>Column space and image of linear map</caption>
   <statement.theorem>
      <para>
         <para.body>Let the <math>
               <latex>(m,n)</latex>
            </math>-matrix <math>
               <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex>
            </math> represent the linear map <math>
               <latex>L\from \RNr[n]\to \RNr[m]</latex>
            </math>. Then <math>
               <latex>\Vect{y}\in \RNr[m]</latex>
            </math> belongs to the image of <math>
               <latex>L</latex>
            </math> if and only if it belongs to the column space of <math>
               <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex>
            </math>.</para.body>
      </para>
   </statement.theorem>
   <proof type="Proof">
      <proof.block>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>We begin by recalling the definitions</para.body>
            </para>
            <ul>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>The image of <math>
                           <latex>L</latex>
                        </math> consists of all those <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{y}</latex>
                        </math> in <math>
                           <latex>\RNr[m]</latex>
                        </math> for which the equation <math>
                           <latex>L(\Vect{x} ) = \Vect{y}</latex>
                        </math> has a solution.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>We know that, for each <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                        </math> in <math>
                           <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
                        </math>, <math>
                           <latex>L(\Vect{x}) = A\cdot \Vect{x}</latex>
                        </math>.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>Thus the image of <math>
                           <latex>L</latex>
                        </math> consists of all those <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{y} \in \RNr[m]</latex>
                        </math> for which the matrix equation <math>
                           <latex>\Mtrx{A}\Vect{x} = \Vect{y}</latex>
                        </math> has a solution. Now, we 
				<subordinate>
                           <hot>know</hot>
                           <crossref>
                              <theorem.ref theoremID="Thm_ColumnSpaceLinearEq"/>
                              <info>
                                 <theorem.ref theoremID="Thm_ColumnSpaceLinearEq"/>
                                 <para>
                                    <para.body>Look up this fact.</para.body>
                                 </para>
                              </info>
                           </crossref>
                        </subordinate>
				that this matrix equation has a solution if and only if <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{y}</latex>
                        </math> is in the column space of <math>
                           <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex>
                        </math>.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
            </ul>
            <para>
               <para.body>This is what we wanted to show.</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
   </proof>
</theorem>
